data.name: ConnectorDiscoveryURLHelp
data.value: This is the URL used by the Mobile Flows server to determine the capabilities of a deployed connector. If you are hosting your connector in the cloud, the publicly accessible URL will be used. If your connector is hosted behind an API or Edge Gateway, then the full path URL of the gateway will be used, to redirect to the connector itself once authenticated. This URL's response must conform to the expected format as defined in the Card Connectors Guide.

data.name: GrantTypeHelp
data.value: Choose from the drop-down list the method of obtaining an access token. Authorization Code is used by confidential and public clients to exchange an authorization code for an access token. This is sometimes called Web App or Web Server in OAuth 2.0 configuration. Client Credentials is used by clients to obtain an access token outside of the context of a user. This is useful if your OAuth 2.0 provider offers a Client Credentials grant type with service account privileges. Password is used by first-party clients to exchange a user’s credentials for an access token. This is useful if your OAuth 2.0 provider offers a Password grant type and you have a service account you want to use.

data.name: HowMobileFlowsWorkDescription
data.value: Mobile Flows allow you to provide employees with the ability to enable or disable actionable notifications through their mobile apps by deploying connectors for each business system you want to connect. Once each connector name is mapped to a public-facing URL for each connector, employees will then have easy access to notifications on their enterprise apps.
